Very cool venue, you will notice as soon as you walk in.
Sleek retro vibe, and dj spinning music.
Very well lit, they are not afraid to show you the interior design.
I have two recommendations for everyone.
For appetizer, the hamachi.
A little jalapeno, garlic, simply delicious.
I am imagining those morsels right now.
The new york strip!!
(served over wasabi demiglace)  The NY Strip is slowly becoming one of my favorite steaks.
This dish is not served like a typical steak, it's served in a log shape, and sliced into about 10 pieces.
The ends were fatty (didn't even eat them) but the rest of the slices were cooked to medium perfection.
Taking each piece and dipping it in the the demiglace, oh myy!!!
Although I am not a huge strip restaurant fan, I put this in the top for the area.
Highly recommended.

