We were at they Wynn for a week long conference and decided to have our team dinner at Andrea's.
Its located inside the Encore and is considered a Fine Dining place.
We walked to the restaurant and they immediately seated us.
The ambiance is amazing, and the service is top notch.
Their menu is very vegetarian friendly.
They are flexible enough to substitute meat with any veggies.
In addition, they have a vegetarian section in their menu that includes sushi rolls, entrees, and sides.
I ordered the following: - Steamed Edamame - Crispy Pan Fried Noodles: I asked them to remove the chicken, and they were very willing.
The noodles were delicious.
- My co-worker order the vegetarian sushi rolls (cucumber, and avocado/asparagus): The sushi rolls were amazing.
I think I liked them more than my noodles.
- For dessert, we ordered a trio ice-cream combo, where we could choose three flavors from a list of 10.
It was delicious.
I would have loved to try other things on their menu, but I just wasn't that hungry.
I would love to go back and try the other vegetarian options on the menu.
Our server was very attentive, and ensured we were well taken care of.
Overall, a great team dinner and a great evening.

